# Types:
#   decision            - Architecture decision record lite
#   feat(spec)          - Add another testable specification/thesis
#   feat(impl)          - Implement a specification/thesis
#   docs                 - Any documentation update
#   deps                 - Changes in dependencies
#   chore                - Scaffolding, cleanup, etc
#   misc                 - Escape hatch
#
# Subject line rules:
#   - Maximum 50 characters
#   - Use imperative mode ("Add registration spec" not "Added registration spec")
#   - No period at the end
#   - Capitalize first letter (unless starting with proper noun/acronym)
#   - Remember this is the envelope, the commit diff is **the message**, so don't repeat yourself in the subject line.
#
# Body rules:
#   - Optional
#   - Note what, explain why
#   - Wrap at 72 characters (recommended)
#   - Use blank lines to separate paragraphs
#   - Remember this is the envelope, the commit diff is **the message**, so don't repeat yourself in the body.
#
# Footer rules:
#   - For feat(spec): Reference related decision or thesis with
#       "Refs: decision <commit-hash>" or "Refs: feat(spec) <commit-hash>"
#   - For feat(impl): Reference specification with
#       "Refs: feat(spec) <commit-hash>"
#   - For decision: Reference related decisions with
#       "Refs: decision <commit-hash>"
#   - Use blank lines to separate multiple footer entries
#   - Optional for other types
